                                                  from Manchester, do the best you can.</orig><note xml:id="f29e7856-1bf0-4d2a-bff9-132c7d08c5c0">Siehe <ref target="B00159">W. R. Cremer an Marx,
                                                  22.8.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170406T114122+0200" comment="{{Br. 155}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?>
                                                  </ref>und
                                                  <?oxy_comment_start author="strauss" timestamp="20170720T180833+0200" comment="Erl. 155a"?><ref target="B00159/#cff67721-5df5-4418-8d4d-9c4d5086166f">Erl.<?oxy_comment_end?></ref></note></seg> Our
                                        prestige is at stake If we can keep away Men the fortune of
                                        our Association is made—Dont mind the expense the Tailors
                                        will pay any amount of money if we can only keep Men away
                                        <pb/> so do act promply.</p><p sameAs="MBTextmitEinzug"><seg type="comment"><orig>The London Secretary of the
              Tailors</orig><note xml:id="cff24302-11e3-4a40-a92f-6b2915cc4dc2"><persName key="ed_rr5_4hk_wy">Mathew Lawrence</persName>.  </note></seg> is here and hopes we
          shall act with vigour.</p><closer sameAs="MBUnterschrift">Fraternally <expan resp="editor" sameAs="dottet_underline">You<ex>rs</ex></expan><lb/>WRCremer </closer></div></body></text></TEI>